Package gep.model

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChromosomalArchitecture<T>
    This class is a factory class to create random Chromosomes.
    Chromosome<T>
    This class implements a Chromosome, which is basically a collection of modifiable and unmodifiable genes linked by a linking function.
    ChromosomeIndependentGeneTerminal<T>
    This class represents a gene terminal whose execution is independent from the chromosome it is included in.
    ExpressionTreeNode<T>
    This class represents a node in a expression tree.
    Gene<T>
    This class represents a gene in gene expression programming.
    GeneArchitecture<T>
    This class is a factory class to create random genes and works as a identifier for genes to test if they were produced by the same architecture and therefore can be genetically merged.
    GeneElement<T>
    This class represents an element in a genes sequence.
    GeneFunction<T>  
    GeneTerminal<T>
    This class represents a gene terminal.
    HomoeoticGeneElement<T>
    This class represents a homoeotic gene terminal.
    Individual<T>
    This class represents an individual with a set of chromosomes and fitness.
    IndividualArchitecture<T>
    This class is a factory class to create random individuals and populations.
